Project No: 0001
Project Name: WelcomeProject (This project focus on only Project Level no App level)
******************************************************
>>> pip install Django

Step 1: Create Django Project 
	Django-admin startproject WelcomeProject

Step 2: Enter into the project 
        cd WelcomeProject 

Step 3: Create templates folder and static folder in project level and modify settings.py accordingly.
WelcomeProject/WelcomeProject/settings.py
-----------------------------------------
#In Templates make a change in 'DIRS' path
'DIRS': [os.path.join(BASE_DIR,'templates')],

#In bottom make a change in Add below line for static files path
STATICFILES_DIRS = [os.path.join(BASE_DIR,'static')]

Step 4: Add image in static folder and add html file in templates folder

#In static folder add logo.png

#In templates folder add t1.html
<b>Hello, {{name}}</b>

#Method 1  ---->For Images
{% load static %}
<img src='{% static "logo.png" %}' alt="img not found">

#Method 2  ----->For images
<img src="/static/logo.png" alt="img not found">

Setp 5: Define view function -- add views.py and add content accordingly
#Process 1: By using Httpresponse
from django.shortcuts import HttpResponse
def m1(request):
    return HttpResponse("Hello, John")

#Process 2: By using render
from django.shortcuts import render
def m1(request):
    return render(request, 't1.html',{'name': 'John'})

Step 6: Define url pattern -- add content in urls.py accordingly
from django.contrib import admin
from django.urls import path
from .views import m1
urlpatterns = [
    path('admin/', admin.site.urls),
    path('',m1),
    #path('extraurl/',m1)
]

Step 7: Start developement server and send HTTP Request
	Py manage.py runserver
	
	http://127.0.0.1:8000/